      <abstract>
        <p>The objective of this study was to describe the first report involving a case of equine acute myonecrosis caused by <italic>C. novyi</italic> type A with an emphasis on clinical signs, the pathological and bacteriological analysis, and molecular identification of the microorganisms as the key of the definitive diagnosis.</p>
      </abstract>
